<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><p>Reading <a href="http://miller.emu.id.au/pmiller/books/rmch/" rel="nofollow">Recursive Make Considered Harmful</a> was a huge help in understanding how <em>make</em> is supposed to work.  The rest of the GNU make tools (<em>autoconf</em>, <em>automake</em>, and so on) seem like overkill for projects that target one OS.  Further, once you know <em>make</em> inside and out, the other tools functionality become more obvious.</p>
</div>
