<a name="75864"></a>
<div id="answer-75864" class="answer" data-answerid="75864" >
    <table>
        <tr>
            <td class="votecell">
                

<div class="vote">
    <input type="hidden" value="75864">
    <a class="vote-up-off" title="This answer is useful">up vote</a>
    <span class="vote-count-post ">0</span>
    <a class="vote-down-off" title="This answer is not useful">down vote</a>
    

</div>

            </td>
            


<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><p>While learning 'make' is loads of fun, recently I've been tinkering with <a href="http://www.scons.org/" rel="nofollow">Scons</a> and it truly makes using make a thing of the past (no pun intended, too many uses of make). Much easier, cross-platform, able to do just about anything Make can do and more. Depends on Python.</p>

<p>Example: Compile all files in a directory into a final binary (SConstruct file)</p>

<pre><code># Will correctly use g++
Program('binaryname', Glob('*.cpp'))
</code></pre>

<p>Example: Build a shared library</p>

<pre><code># Build a new shared library, libtest.so from all .c files
# If you were windows you'd get test.dll
SharedLibrary('test', Glob('*.c'))
</code></pre>

<p>Magic!</p>
</div>
    <table class="fw">
    <tr>
    <td class="vt">










